result.execSummary:
The defendant Standice C Jiles was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Standice C Jiles is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Standice C Jiles was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

As to Count 2:    Defendant  pled to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to her plea, Court finds based on the colloquy held by Branch 22 on 7/1/2015  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  As to Count 1:   Due to withdrawal of the guilty plea, and pursuant to negotiations and on motion of the State Court DISMISSED the charge.
Court ordered a forfeiture of $300.00 plus costs to be paid at $100.00/month commencing 1/15/2016 to be paid on the 15th of each month until paid in full.  Any missed payments and the entire amount becomes due and owing to convert to a civil judgment.
  Court finds the defendant was under the age of 25 at the time of the offense, the charge is a misdemeanor, society would not be harmed and the defendant would benefit by expungement.  Court grants expungement upon successful completion of payment of forfeiture and costs as ordered.

Filed, original amended information; copy served on defendant.  Defendant acknowledges receipt of information, waives formal reading, pleads not guilty.  
Court ordered addition of Count 2 , contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 946.41(1), 939.51(3)(a) , a Class A.
